1
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:50,080
With the utmost respect, miss,
I've contacted the hospital

2
00:02:50,160 --> 00:02:52,600
to send a nurse
to check your condition again

3
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:54,040
just to make sure
you don't have any injuries.

4
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:56,400
Oh, it's alright, Mr. Supol.

5
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:59,080
I'm fine. I'm not hurt at all.
There's really no need.

6
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:05,760
I may have made some mistakes before,
so I feel bad.

7
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:07,600
Please let me take care of you.

8
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:11,200
But you've always
taken care of me, haven't you?

9
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,240
Well, but…

10
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:16,120
Mr. Supol taking care of you before

11
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:20,760
and taking care of you now as Grandma's…

12
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:23,800
real granddaughter,

13
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:26,960
is different.

14
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:33,240
Mr. Supol, I'm still the same Kluay.

15
00:03:33,320 --> 00:03:36,640
I haven't changed at all.

16
00:03:36,720 --> 00:03:39,000
So, can you

17
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:41,800
treat me the same way
you did on the first day?

18
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,040
Yes, miss.

19
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:46,640
Miss again, Mr. Supol?

20
00:03:46,720 --> 00:03:49,760
Just call me Kluay. I'm not used to it.

21
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:52,440
- Alright.
- Yes. Kluay.

22
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:55,120
Try to understand him.

23
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:59,880
He's been waiting to take care of you
for over 20 years. Right?

24
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:01,560
Yes.

25
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:05,480
Just because I have Grandma's bloodline

26
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:08,320
doesn't mean everything has to change.

27
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,600
Well…

28
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:11,080
Don't think like that.

29
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:15,040
Everyone has different roles in life.

30
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:17,040
It's not the same.

31
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,800
Grandma has always
taken good care of Mr. Supol.

32
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:24,680
Now that he has the chance
to take care of her real granddaughter,

33
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:30,120
it's like
he's repaying her kindness. Right?

34
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,320
That's right.

35
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:35,600
I'll pretend I understand.

36
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,920
Where's Grandma?

37
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:42,560
- Well, right now…
- She's in the hospital.

38
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,160
What happened to her?

39
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,920
She's fine now. She's safe.

40
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:53,200
Should we go visit her?

41
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:57,240
No. The doctor wants her to rest.

42
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,200
We can probably pick her up tomorrow.

43
00:05:02,280 --> 00:05:05,560
Okay. Then we'll go together tomorrow.

44
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:14,800
Mr. Warat,

45
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:19,160
how are you so sure that I'm Waree?

46
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:22,920
Mm.

47
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:28,280
Som and Arnon have already prepared
all the evidence

48
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:32,040
and documents for you.

49
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:35,000
When you're ready,
we can go look together.

50
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:41,440
Mr. Supol, do you want to come?

51
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:45,000
I'll excuse myself.

52
00:05:45,080 --> 00:05:48,120
Please go see it.
I've already seen all the evidence.

53
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:50,760
May I call you Ms. Kluay?

54
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:55,640
- That's fine.
- Yes, Ms. Kluay.

55
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:58,040
Come see it with us.

56
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,160
Oh.

57
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:02,880
No, I won't go. My eyesight isn't good.
If it's dark, I won't be able to see.

58
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:04,920
- Are you sure? Alright.
- Please.

59
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:22,040
If Warat dies,

60
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:24,360
all the shares will go to Uncle Rut.

61
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:28,800
And…

62
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:31,480
where is Uncle Rut?

63
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:34,280
Didn't you say
you brought him back already?

64
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:36,400
And what if Uncle Rut dies?

65
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:42,440
You mean…

66
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:45,880
Then all the shares will go to us.

67
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:48,720
Sin,

68
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:54,000
we only have each other in this family.

69
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:56,520
What are you going to do about Warat?

70
00:06:57,560 --> 00:07:01,200
If you want to catch a fish,
you need bait.

71
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:15,240
And the best bait for a small fish

72
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:18,240
is the big fish, its father.

73
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:37,960
What is this?

74
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:42,120
These are all the documents proving that

75
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,800
you are Waree.

76
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:47,440
This is the anklet
you've had since childhood.

77
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:50,640
Mm.

78
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:51,840
And this…

79
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:55,080
is Mr. Warat's anklet.

80
00:07:57,560 --> 00:08:01,400
No wonder when I first saw your anklet,

81
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:02,760
it felt familiar.

82
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:16,400
Are you done with work already?
It's only noon.

83
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:18,880
I snuck away from my mom.

84
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:20,240
She might fire you.

85
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:24,680
If she fires her only beloved son,

86
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:27,600
who's going to take care of Vanich Mall?

87
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,840
Oh? Mom,

88
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:33,480
there's someone skipping work here.

89
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,520
I'll go back soon.

90
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:40,159
- I just came to give you something.
- Hm?

91
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:42,000
It was just finished.

92
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:44,640
Here.

93
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:52,800
Hey.

94
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,720
I had it made specially for you.

95
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,880
You didn't have to go to all that trouble.

96
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:03,760
It's not trouble. I told you, didn't I?

97
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:07,240
I'll take care of you
and our child for the rest of my life.

98
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:09,120
This is nothing.

99
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:11,120
Thank you.

100
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:13,960
Consider it a return gift

101
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:17,880
for melting your gold
to make an anklet for our child.

102
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:31,480
What? Did you see something?

103
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:38,400
Mr. Warat,
I saw you as a child, with Waree.

104
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,880
Did we grow up together?

105
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:52,440
Aunt Nong,

106
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,240
what are we going to do about Uncle Rut?

107
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:59,200
Once the bait has served its purpose,
we discard it.

108
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,160
Aunt Nong.

109
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,240
Aunt Nong.

110
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:17,440
I know

111
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:20,880
what Sarut is thinking.

112
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:27,240
But what he doesn't know
is what I'm thinking.

113
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:32,200
He's always believed he's important,

114
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:37,760
when in fact, he's nothing.

115
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:47,880
Mm.

116
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:51,240
The only important person to me

117
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:56,560
is you, Sin.

118
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,360
Auntie, so…

119
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:02,400
what will you do about Uncle Rut?

120
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:07,080
Tomorrow,

121
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:11,400
we'll lure Warat to our house

122
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,800
and deal with both of them.

123
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,640
After that, all the shares

124
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:21,520
will belong to us.

125
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:26,960
And what about the bodies?

126
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:32,920
Warat already knows

127
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,960
Sarut is his father.

128
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:38,960
And now he's filled with anger.

129
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:43,240
What are you talking about?

130
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:45,400
I'm talking about

131
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:49,800
the news that will come out tomorrow.

132
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:53,960
Warat came to our house

133
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:56,160
and shot Uncle Rut.

134
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:58,480
Uncle Rut

135
00:11:58,560 --> 00:12:01,040
fought back and shot him.

136
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:06,720
They both got shot

137
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:11,920
and died from their wounds.

138
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:17,400
They both died.

139
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:39,560
This is the condition of the car
on the day of the incident,

140
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:43,040
the same day
you and your mother disappeared.

141
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,480
This is the DNA report

142
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:50,120
from the unidentified bodies foundation.

143
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:53,000
It states that the bodies in the car

144
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,720
were Pong and Soi.

145
00:12:56,520 --> 00:13:01,920
And this is a photo Dad took
of the car where he found you that day.

146
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:04,480
It's the same car.

147
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:06,560
And this.

148
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:09,520
I just found it. Another photo Dad took.

149
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:14,360
The necklace?

150
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,640
It's this necklace.

151
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:21,080
That means Ms. Ampha was in that car,

152
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:24,200
trapped inside it.

153
00:13:28,560 --> 00:13:32,480
But why would she try
to communicate with you

154
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:35,000
through dreams?

155
00:13:37,600 --> 00:13:42,720
Maybe, what she's been
trying to tell me all along

156
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:45,800
is that…

157
00:13:47,920 --> 00:13:49,920
she wants me to take care of you,

158
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,800
to protect you as best as I can.

159
00:13:58,160 --> 00:14:00,440
Ah!

160
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:02,600
- You possessed kid!
- You possessed kid!

161
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:30,360
Are you okay?

162
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,200
Are you okay?

163
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:37,320
I'm fine.

164
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:39,200
You should go.

165
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:42,200
Stay away from me. I don't want…

166
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:46,200
Hey.

167
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:50,600
Teacher?

168
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:54,440
You should go.
Just leave me here. I'll be fine.

169
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:13,920
What grade are you in?

170
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,160
Fourth grade.

171
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:18,200
I'm in sixth grade.

172
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:20,240
If anyone bullies you, call me.

173
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:35,360
Warat, when we were kids,

174
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:43,000
do you remember the girl
who got teased for seeing ghosts?

175
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:49,840
Don't tell me…

176
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:53,000
That was me.

177
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:58,280
So we've been close
to each other all along?

178
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:06,360
Thank you for always protecting me.

179
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:14,000
The woman I've been seeing…

180
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,680
Ms. Kluay,

181
00:16:16,560 --> 00:16:18,240
have you been seeing her since childhood?

182
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:20,760
Yes, she has.

183
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:25,240
Ms. Ampha has always been by your side.

184
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:30,360
Then are you here now?

185
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:38,760
The last time I saw her…

186
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:44,960
Could something have happened?

187
00:16:45,760 --> 00:16:47,080
Kluay.

188
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:49,320
Let's go.

189
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:16,839
Anong. Sin.

190
00:17:19,520 --> 00:17:20,400
Hey.

191
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:23,560
What are you two doing to me?

192
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:30,640
It's a pity. At first,

193
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:34,160
I was going to bring Praewilai
to stay here with you.

194
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,000
But…

195
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,440
Praewilai…

196
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:44,400
What did you do to her?

197
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:45,880
Huh?

198
00:17:48,480 --> 00:17:50,240
These past ten years,

199
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:52,760
what have you really been doing, Anong?

200
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:57,320
Don't worry

201
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:05,040
because I've brought Ampha
to stay here with you too.

202
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:14,640
What did you do to Praewilai, Anong?!

203
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:21,760
Do you really want to know?

204
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:25,040
What did Rut tell you?

205
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:29,240
Calm down. I'll tell you.

206
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:31,440
Mr. Rut

207
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:34,920
said he's changed his plan.

208
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:38,960
He told you to tell me that?

209
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:40,920
So what is he going to do?

210
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:44,320
He said you don't have to endure anymore.

211
00:18:44,920 --> 00:18:48,000
What about everything he made me endure

212
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:51,040
so Warat could inherit the Vanich fortune?

213
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:55,280
Mr. Rut said

214
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:58,200
he's realized
that the woman he truly loves

215
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:00,360
is you.

216
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:03,240
- Anong, I…
- So he said

217
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:07,000
he wants you to bring Warat
to live with him,

218
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:10,160
as one family.

219
00:19:10,840 --> 00:19:12,320
Where are you going, Anong?

220
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:13,960
Anong.

221
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:17,400
I just…

222
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:21,200
wanted to ask

223
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:25,520
if you know
I'm in love with Mr. Sarut, right?

224
00:19:26,280 --> 00:19:28,360
Where are you going?

225
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:37,280
I just came to congratulate you

226
00:19:39,760 --> 00:19:42,000
for getting everything.

227
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:44,440
What are you doing?

228
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:54,400
I…

229
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:59,160
I'm the one who lost everything.

230
00:20:02,080 --> 00:20:03,640
From my sister

231
00:20:06,040 --> 00:20:07,600
to…

232
00:20:09,160 --> 00:20:11,240
the man I loved the most.

233
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:14,080
Calm down, Anong.

234
00:20:14,160 --> 00:20:17,120
Don't do this. Don't think like this.

235
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:18,760
Take it.

236
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:22,160
Just take it. Take it all.

237
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:23,920
I don't want anything anymore.

238
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:27,880
Take my life too. I don't want it anymore.

239
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:30,120
Don't do this.

240
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:33,280
Of course.

241
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:36,400
You can say that.

242
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:42,400
You're the one who got everything.

243
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:50,480
I…

244
00:20:51,840 --> 00:20:54,000
I'm sorry about Naree.

245
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:56,680
I'm sorry about Sarut.

246
00:20:57,520 --> 00:20:59,520
I'm really sorry, Anong.

247
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:03,560
If there's anything I can do
to make it up to you,

248
00:21:03,640 --> 00:21:05,320
I will.

249
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:10,640
There is.

250
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:26,040
Prae…

251
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:29,120
Don't waste your breath crying for her.

252
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:32,400
You'll be with her soon enough.

253
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:36,800
Anong, what have you done?

254
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:39,720
What have you done? I took care of you

255
00:21:39,800 --> 00:21:42,960
- for ten years!
- I'm the one who took care of you!

256
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:45,240
What do you want?

257
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:48,480
Tell me, what do you want?

258
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:55,760
Please, Anong, let me go.

259
00:21:58,240 --> 00:21:59,400
I'm begging you.

260
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:03,480
I'm begging you. Let me go.

261
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:18,720
Do you want to live?

262
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:25,160
Let me go. Tell me what you want.

263
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:29,040
I'll do anything. What do you want?
Tell me, Anong.

264
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:31,120
Do you want to live?

265
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:49,160
Bow to me.

266
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:53,280
Bow!

267
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:29,600
Mr. Rut. Mr. Rut.

268
00:23:30,760 --> 00:23:32,160
What?

269
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:35,400
Mr. Rut, the arrogant one.

270
00:23:36,040 --> 00:23:37,360
The proud one.

271
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:42,640
Mr. Rut, who thinks
he's smarter than everyone.

272
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:46,960
You want to live?

273
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:56,280
Anong.

274
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:59,480
Please let me go.

275
00:24:00,760 --> 00:24:01,920
Let me go, Anong.

276
00:24:04,240 --> 00:24:05,080
I'm begging you.

277
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:11,880
It's not your time yet.

278
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:15,760
If you die now,

279
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:19,960
the fish won't bite the bait.

280
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:25,000
What do you mean?

281
00:24:27,640 --> 00:24:29,160
Call Warat here.

282
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:41,040
Mom?

283
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:46,080
Where are you?

284
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:14,880
Call Warat here now.

285
00:25:18,360 --> 00:25:20,000
You've already lost your dignity anyway!

286
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:33,880
Mr. Rut.

287
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:38,600
My dear Rut.

288
00:25:41,360 --> 00:25:42,720
Do you know

289
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:48,280
that your car accident…

290
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:53,600
was no accident at all?

291
00:26:03,560 --> 00:26:04,960
What do you mean?

292
00:26:08,920 --> 00:26:11,720
Kaew said you could do anything.

293
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:13,120
Yes, Nong.

294
00:26:13,720 --> 00:26:17,000
If not dead, can you make him disabled?

295
00:26:20,320 --> 00:26:21,200
That's difficult.

296
00:26:24,680 --> 00:26:26,160
Which part do you want disabled?

297
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:33,200
Anong, was that you?

298
00:26:39,280 --> 00:26:40,520
Now,

299
00:26:41,640 --> 00:26:45,840
I've told you everything
you needed to hear.

300
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:51,720
Now it's your turn.

301
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:55,760
You should do

302
00:26:57,040 --> 00:27:00,160
what you're supposed to do.

303
00:27:02,240 --> 00:27:03,760
No?

304
00:27:06,520 --> 00:27:07,560
No!

305
00:27:08,120 --> 00:27:10,000
Stop stalling!

306
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:15,200
Sin. Should we do it?

307
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:23,240
Ms. Kluay has been asleep for hours.
Will she really see her?

308
00:27:23,320 --> 00:27:25,520
Sometimes she can't communicate with her.

309
00:27:26,280 --> 00:27:27,800
But sometimes,

310
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:30,400
Ms. Ampha just appears when she wants to.

311
00:27:31,520 --> 00:27:32,960
So,

312
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:35,840
now that she suddenly disappeared,
that means…

313
00:27:37,200 --> 00:27:40,360
Could someone have done something to her?

314
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:46,400
<i>If you want to help your father,</i>

315
00:27:46,480 --> 00:27:48,360
<i>you must come alone tonight.</i>

316
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:58,520
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

317
00:27:58,600 --> 00:28:01,360
<i>This is my fault. My selfishness.</i>

318
00:28:02,120 --> 00:28:04,640
I was jealous of Wichan. Jealous of Ampha.

319
00:28:05,560 --> 00:28:09,600
But back then, I didn't understand.
I really didn't.

320
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:12,320
Why did Wichan get to be happy?

321
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:17,480
He was born in the right place,
at the right time, to the right people.

322
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:20,680
<i>While I…</i>

323
00:28:22,080 --> 00:28:25,480
<i>For me to have anything at all,</i>

324
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:27,000
<i>to get to where I am today,</i>

325
00:28:27,960 --> 00:28:31,120
I did every dirty thing.

326
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:35,320
I was bitter.

327
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:38,800
<i>Bitter that</i>

328
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:42,360
<i>I wasn't rich like everyone else.</i>

329
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:46,800
<i>But I kept all that bitterness inside.</i>

330
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:56,000
<i>Stop rambling and get to the point. Hurry!</i>

331
00:29:00,240 --> 00:29:01,440
<i>Warat,</i>

332
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:05,640
<i>today may be my last day.</i>

333
00:29:08,280 --> 00:29:11,000
<i>I understand now. I finally understand.</i>

334
00:29:11,680 --> 00:29:14,120
<i>Everything I've done,</i>

335
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:17,360
<i>none of it matters.</i>

336
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:23,480
<i>It means nothing at all.</i>
<i>The most important thing…</i>

337
00:29:24,160 --> 00:29:25,800
<i>is you.</i>

338
00:29:25,880 --> 00:29:28,480
<i>Warat, remember this.</i>

339
00:29:29,080 --> 00:29:31,320
<i>You are my only son.</i>

340
00:29:34,120 --> 00:29:35,760
You're losing your mind.

341
00:29:37,720 --> 00:29:40,920
You're my only son. If I could go back…

342
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:44,280
If I could go back…

343
00:29:45,040 --> 00:29:48,320
<i>- I would never choose this path.</i>
<i>- Enough. Enough already.</i>

344
00:29:48,840 --> 00:29:52,000
<i>See, Warat? Your father has gone senile.</i>

345
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:54,120
<i>Listen to me. Listen.</i>

346
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:56,680
<i>Come make a deal with me alone,</i>

347
00:29:57,360 --> 00:30:00,280
<i>and everyone will be safe.</i>
<i>If you try anything…</i>

348
00:30:00,360 --> 00:30:03,120
<i>- Don't talk. Shut up!</i>
<i>- Warat…</i>

349
00:30:03,200 --> 00:30:05,360
<i>I wish I had more time with you.</i>

350
00:30:05,440 --> 00:30:07,440
<i>- Warat.</i>
<i>- If you try anything…</i>

351
00:30:07,520 --> 00:30:08,920
<i>- Don't come, Warat.</i>
<i>- …your father won't make it out alive.</i>

352
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:12,200
<i>They planned this.</i>
<i>They're going to kill you and me.</i>

353
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:13,360
<i>Don't come!</i>

354
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:21,240
Do you think Warat will come?

355
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:24,960
Someone as arrogant as Warat
will definitely come.

356
00:30:25,040 --> 00:30:27,280
Tell him not to come,
and he'll come anyway.

357
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:30,680
Tell him to bring the police,
and he'll come alone.

358
00:30:31,280 --> 00:30:32,160
Good.

359
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:36,680
That deserves a reward.

360
00:30:45,840 --> 00:30:46,920
Please…

361
00:30:50,360 --> 00:30:52,000
Don't hurt Warat.

362
00:30:52,080 --> 00:30:53,920
We'll soon find out

363
00:30:54,920 --> 00:30:57,360
whether Warat cares about you or not.

364
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:05,440
<i>Listen to me.</i>
<i>Come make a deal with me alone,</i>

365
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:07,800
<i>and everyone will be safe.</i>

366
00:31:30,440 --> 00:31:31,400
Warat, my son!

367
00:31:31,480 --> 00:31:34,400
What did you do to my son? Help!

368
00:31:35,760 --> 00:31:36,720
Mr. Warat.

369
00:31:37,360 --> 00:31:39,560
Mr. Warat. Mr. Warat.

370
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:41,720
Mr. Warat.

371
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:42,640
Kluay…

372
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:44,000
Hang in there.

373
00:31:44,080 --> 00:31:45,360
I'll…

374
00:31:45,440 --> 00:31:48,240
I'll call an ambulance. Mr. Warat.

375
00:31:48,960 --> 00:31:50,040
Mr. Warat!

376
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:59,240
Mr. Warat? What happened?

377
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:39,240
Where did Mr. Warat go?

378
00:32:47,320 --> 00:32:49,640
Oh, Ms. Kluay, you're awake?

379
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:52,800
<i>Are you with Mr. Warat?</i>

380
00:32:52,880 --> 00:32:54,640
Som and I

381
00:32:54,720 --> 00:32:58,280
<i>saw that you were asleep,</i>
<i>so we came back to Baan Saeng.</i>

382
00:32:58,880 --> 00:33:00,720
Mr. Warat isn't with you?

383
00:33:01,640 --> 00:33:05,040
No. I saw a sign.

384
00:33:05,120 --> 00:33:08,120
Another sign? What did you see?

385
00:33:09,920 --> 00:33:12,760
Kluay, it's Som. What did you see?

386
00:33:13,360 --> 00:33:15,760
Som, I saw Mr. Warat get shot.

387
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:37,160
Hello, Mr. Arnon.

388
00:33:37,240 --> 00:33:39,800
Mr. Supol, is Mr. Warat with you?

389
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:41,640
No, he isn't.

390
00:33:41,720 --> 00:33:43,040
Mr. Warat is missing.

391
00:33:43,120 --> 00:33:46,120
What? He's missing again?

392
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:48,960
If you see him,
please tell me immediately.

393
00:33:49,040 --> 00:33:50,760
Yes. Alright.

394
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:58,280
- Mr. Warat…
- Kluay.

395
00:33:58,840 --> 00:34:01,840
Som, Mr. Arnon,
let's go to Mr. Sarut's house.

396
00:34:01,920 --> 00:34:03,520
Mr. Warat is at Mr. Sarut's house?

397
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:05,200
Why Sarut's house?

398
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:09,000
I don't know. I saw it in the sign.

399
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:12,679
It was a room, full of terrifying things.

400
00:34:13,280 --> 00:34:16,000
What does that have to do
with Sarut's house?

401
00:34:16,080 --> 00:34:18,440
You've been there before.
Was there a room like that?

402
00:34:18,520 --> 00:34:20,360
No.

403
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:26,360
I don't know, but I feel like
there's something there. We have to go.

404
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:27,800
Alright.

405
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:31,040
Then let's go to Sarut's house.

406
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:40,760
Warat?

407
00:34:43,199 --> 00:34:44,159
Warat, watch out!

408
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:47,360
- Ugh!
- Warat, my son!

409
00:34:47,440 --> 00:34:49,199
What did you do to my son?

410
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:51,840
Help! Help! Warat!

411
00:35:05,160 --> 00:35:08,240
Arnon, if it really is Sarut's house,

412
00:35:08,320 --> 00:35:10,680
then Jirasin must be involved.

413
00:35:11,680 --> 00:35:12,920
Sin?

414
00:35:14,040 --> 00:35:14,920
Yes.

415
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:18,880
Ms. Kluay, do you know yet?
Chatchai was fired.

416
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:22,480
What? Mr. Chatchai was fired?

417
00:35:22,560 --> 00:35:26,520
I showed Mrs. Wanee the information
you gave me and the CCTV footage.

418
00:35:27,120 --> 00:35:28,560
What CCTV footage?

419
00:35:28,640 --> 00:35:30,960
I secretly hid a camera in the office.

420
00:35:32,760 --> 00:35:33,680
It caught solid evidence.

421
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,080
Explain.

422
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:38,400
Who is the man in this photo?

423
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:40,360
I was following Mr. Jirasin's orders.

424
00:35:40,440 --> 00:35:41,840
Go pack your things.

425
00:35:42,520 --> 00:35:43,360
Yes.

426
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:45,960
Or do you want to sit here

427
00:35:46,760 --> 00:35:48,320
until the police…

428
00:35:56,400 --> 00:35:58,280
Oh, I have a good plan.

429
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:11,440
- Why are you calling me?
- We know each other. Why can't I call you?

430
00:36:11,520 --> 00:36:12,720
I don't want to know you.

431
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:14,960
I know you're not the real culprit.

432
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:17,280
<i>It was all Jirasin, right?</i>

433
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:19,240
The forged documents and everything else.

434
00:36:19,840 --> 00:36:20,640
What are you talking about?

435
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:23,720
I want to know where Jirasin is right now.

436
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:24,600
Why do you want to know?

437
00:36:24,680 --> 00:36:27,200
I have something to discuss with him.

438
00:36:28,160 --> 00:36:30,600
- If that's all--
<i>- Your job and your future.</i>

439
00:36:30,680 --> 00:36:33,600
I can talk to Mrs. Wanee
and get you reinstated.

440
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:37,720
Why are you offering me this?

441
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:40,360
I'm afraid something will happen
at Jirasin's house.

442
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:43,800
- What about Mr. Sin?
- Go talk to him.

443
00:36:43,880 --> 00:36:45,120
That's all?

444
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:49,720
Yes. If you can stop him
from fighting with Mr. Warat,

445
00:36:49,800 --> 00:36:53,520
<i>I'll ask Mrs. Wanee</i>
<i>to bring you back to work.</i>

446
00:37:24,080 --> 00:37:25,160
My son.

447
00:37:25,920 --> 00:37:28,880
How are you? Are you hurt?

448
00:37:31,120 --> 00:37:32,160
Sin.

449
00:37:34,520 --> 00:37:35,800
Didn't you say

450
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:39,200
we were going to negotiate nicely.

451
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:41,320
There's nothing left for us to negotiate.

452
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:43,160
Sin, Anong,

453
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:46,640
please let my son go. Please.

454
00:37:47,440 --> 00:37:48,840
At least we lived together once.

455
00:37:48,920 --> 00:37:49,920
- Let go…
- Let go?

456
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:52,400
Let go of what?

457
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:57,120
Sin.

458
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:04,560
The reason Warat ended up like this

459
00:38:04,640 --> 00:38:06,320
is because of you.

460
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:08,080
NEXT EPISODE

461
00:38:08,160 --> 00:38:10,200
Promise me one thing, both of you.

462
00:38:10,280 --> 00:38:12,440
If anything happens,

463
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:16,160
run away immediately.

464
00:38:17,320 --> 00:38:18,760
Kluay, why are you here?

465
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:20,720
Ms. Anong!

466
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:22,240
- Ms. Anong.
- Aunt Nong.

467
00:38:24,920 --> 00:38:26,040
Ms. Anong.

468
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:27,840
Anong, don't!

469
00:38:29,680 --> 00:38:30,520
Hey.

470
00:38:31,640 --> 00:38:32,960
Chatchai.

471
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:36,560
Now the power is in my hands, not yours.

472
00:38:37,640 --> 00:38:38,880
All of you will die today.

473
00:38:39,480 --> 00:38:41,320
- No! Don't.
- Sin!

474
00:41:06,360 --> 00:41:08,360
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
